"Around hundreds of mines had to be removed or destroyed," said Jens Müller, spokesman of Nord Stream.
In addition, intensified measures to protect the fauna and flora had to be taken.
The line is a long metal snake, heavy like 242 Eiffel towers, which has been interrupted by nothing throughout the entire length: neither by valves, nor maintenance stations.
